The book also provides extensive coverage of acoustic radiation including acoustic interaction between the transducers. The book is inherently multidisciplinary. It provides essential background regarding the vibration of elastic passive and piezoelectric bodies, piezoelectricity, acoustic radiation, and transducer characterization. Scientists and engineers working in the field of electroacoustics and those involved in education in the field will find this material useful not only for underwater acoustics, but also for electromechanics, energy conversion and medical ultrasonics. Part I contains an introduction to the energy method illustrated with examples of one degree of freedom transducers. It is self-sufficient and can be read independently.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPiezoelectric transducers. 0aUnderwater acoustics. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Acoustics & Sound.2bisacsh  aAcoustic Transduction.  aelectroacoustics.  aelectromechanical circuits.  apiezoelectric transducers.  aunderwater sound.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076741408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644698259?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644698259zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644698259/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076741-4 Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA